answers.body_markdown:
`services` needs to `return` `fetch`. Fetch returns a promise, so handling the promise and response should happen in your route before render is called.

```
module.exports = {
    services: () =&gt; fetch( /* your fetch code */)
}

// Then in your routes...
router.get(&#39;/&#39;, async (req, res) =&gt; {
    const resp = await records.services()
    const serviceRecord = await resp.json()
    res.render(&quot;landing&quot;, { serviceRecord });
});
```

Also, someone mentioned just using await inside of your services function, which is totally doable, too.

```
module.exports = {
    services: async () =&gt; {
        const response = await fetch( /* your fetch code */)
        return await response.json()
    }

}

// Then in your routes...
router.get(&#39;/&#39;, async (req, res) =&gt; {
    const serviceRecord = await records.services()
    res.render(&quot;landing&quot;, { serviceRecord });
});
```

